com.salesforce.omakase.parser.token

Interface ConstantEnum

  • All Known Implementing Classes:
    AttributeMatchType, MediaRestriction

    public interface ConstantEnum
    Very similar to a TokenEnum, except that this is used for enums that must match more than one character (a constant) as opposed to a single token.

    By adding this interface to an Enum it allows a value to be easily parsed to the correct Enum member using Source#optionalFromConstantEnum(Class).

    TokenEnum should be preferred over this if possible as matching a single token is more performant than matching a constant.

      • caseSensitive

        boolean caseSensitive()
        Whether the constant is case-sensitive. Returning true is more performant.

        Important: if returning false (not case-sensitive), the value from constant() must be lower-cased.

        Returns:
        True if the constant is case-sensitive, e.g., must match exactly.
